By https://github.com/junaruga/rpm-py-installer/pull/78 , 
Removing `rpm-devel` dependency is going to be success, maybe.

But how to handle `/usr/include/popt.h` (popt-devel) is used in `rpmlib.h`?

Search the dependency packages by below way, and download the RPM by dnf download plugin or `yumdownloader`, and use the header files in the building process.

It is a kind of `map` process of `map-reduce`.

```
$ grep -r '^#include' include/rpm/ | cut -d: -f 2 | grep -v rpm | sort | uniq
